          <avActivityHighlights>Low avalanche danger will prevail.</avActivityHighlights>
          <avActivityComment>As a consequence of warming during the day only isolated wet avalanches are possible. &lt;br/&gt; &lt;br/&gt; Only isolated dry avalanches are possible. They can be released, in particular by large loads, but they will be small in most cases. Individual avalanche prone locations are to be found on steep shady slopes at high altitude.</avActivityComment>
          <snowpackStructureComment>Shady slopes: Avalanche prone weak layers exist in the old snowpack in particular on northwest, north and northeast facing slopes. &lt;br/&gt; &lt;br/&gt; Outgoing longwave radiation during the night will be severely restricted. As a consequence of high relative humidity the snowpack can not consolidate. Sunny slopes: The weather conditions gave rise to moistening of the snowpack.</snowpackStructureComment>
